4 HJR___ RECOGNIZING THE NEED FOR A NORTH-SOUTH TRANSPORTATION
5 ROUTE IN EAST ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, there is a strong economic need to have a
8 four-lane north-south transportation route that connects
9 East Alabama to the Port of Mobile, particularly due to the
10 amount of manufacturing in Talladega, Calhoun, and Etowah
11 Counties; and
12 WHEREAS, currently, East Alabama only has access to
13 Interstates 59, 20, and 85, which run east-west; a
14 north-south route in the eastern counties of Alabama would
15 be a more direct route to the Port of Mobile and the
16 transportation of goods; and
17 WHEREAS, a north-south route would connect the
18 economies and communities of East Alabama; and
19 WHEREAS, a north-south route would benefit the
20 economy of the state overall, including creating another
21 route that accesses Alabama's beautiful gulf coast, which
22 will increase tourism and serve to relieve congestion on
23 I-65 and the other north-south routes in the state; now
24 therefore,
25 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
26 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That this body recognizes the
27 necessity to create north-south transportation
Page 1

necessity to create north-south transportation
